 At least 4,300 Kerio Valley landowners who will be displaced for fluorspar mining will be compensated before June, an inter-ministerial team has revealed Committee has been formed to verify the list of beneficiaries. National Lands Commission official Silas Kinoti said President Uhuru Kenyatta orderd the compensation last year. Kinoti said residents have no title deeds, prompting formation of a verification team. It is to complete work before the end of the month. Kenya Flourspar Company had suspended mining operations. Marakwet Deputy Governor Wesley Rotich urged the state to revive mining to create jobs.